ct.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking API filters**\\n\\nI’m trying to figure out if getFilters is a public API. It seems like it is, as it relates to QueryableRequestSpecification. But then I’m wondering about filter equality—do I need to hold instances for that? I see that I can build a merged RequestSpecification by adding a couple of filters and another specification. I should check if the method to get defined filters works correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XmUJaE3giV7FOb8h1Q6ScTyN|fc_00568a70dbcee86d016a28015adfa48194af644d605beecb1b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -n \"Filter\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/main/extracted/io/restassured/specification/QueryableRequestSpecification.java | head -30 && grep -n \"get.*Filter\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/main/extracted/io/restassured/specification/QueryableRequestSpecification.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2203, "output": 1480, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35939, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781006646869, "responseId": "resp_00568a70dbcee86d016a28013750648194a4dd85f82d956906"}}
