[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying Groovy methods**\n\nI’m contemplating whether `thisFilters.removeAll(instanceOfAuthFilter)` in Groovy uses `DefaultGroovyMethods.removeAll(Collection, Closure)` or if it calls `Collection.removeAll(Collection)`. I think the argument being a Closure might mean that the signature for `Collection.removeAll(Collection<?>)` isn't being applied here, leaving the DefaultGroovyMethods as the appropriate choice. It's interesting to parse through these method overloads and figure out which one is in play!\n\n**Analyzing class testing**\n\nIt seems the entire library isn't tracked, which isn't helpful. I think we should implement a more explicit test method that loads the closure class and invokes it via `LambdaMetafactory` without relying on public behavior. We already check after public behavior. \n\nI should also verify if the closure passed to `removeAll` is not closure3 but closure4. I’ll check the numbering and see if the assertion might fail if it’s not closure3. This could be a tougher problem to solve.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00568a70dbcee86d016a2802e1e3e08194b8b71775f8ba4b71\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKAML_lAA5EKqI4c3jAN7NeLMZBlMncwkNBp9fSfXNLJryS7o1KqNTdVSJ5uXh-Y1kagdf0mic--jYhnjb9aZX6CZkkkeLLxF_wAmj31ci3NZ9kRYqHfFPM73PLTINhkxlm8w6xiuPOth2pd59P-708Hs-e24zzEbKNYlJQonLTHpVGOT0d8KtHx4lPfr0OKvo3IwWjlFXO-2TFCifoNYbkNulN-il5h1XdzFFd1nUDjLkcDs6BxVEUjeTJDeDHRMUhhKcqCfexD7JA7pek8Wpc7-ZBNhSBZplnzIjTHX9MfSkPuOAVOmrKd0adszk65NI6BE5OTGcTMZTUfneiwUNmgXC8zfs-uSrfAZfOZRag9vBYd3IBKmbWVLQ4PBCMRq7hKHnOkg2QoiW5zlIcfUuVn_zFeUKG41ma_p4u_zwQF-akPMT_U9PjdiMQN8IInoDl0kgPdPuggiKarCUNhzBGq3GyCxq4s7Hzgj-AgAMA7u-_XxSXOJvwLtmvyPakXSmGRUZN6YVtmQ6IxlayBWZ3R1uDeUebdORwDdGKzkEoD8JiLUcMMAFbdABouIam6ugK1B_MvjNyPaA2RmFYloffDDrZUhCUMJdbo-2WuQ-jnKKmtiT1c5qpv_I6qmr7BHtWMcH7Ufpul8HGB3nq73q20eKBinTMnm0ALh8FfjgH0poXRWWncRPDsofSUTuxO8